What is unit testing? Unit testing is the execution of a complete class, routine or small program
Unit testing is conducted by the developer
It is type of (blackbox/whitebox testing) whitebox

What is integration testing? Testing the combined execution of 2 or more classes, packages, components or subsystems
Integration testing is conducted by testers and test integration software
It is a type of (blackbox/whitebox testing) blackbox


System testing 

What is system Testing?
System testing is the execution of the software in its final configuration, including
integration with other software and hardware systems. It tests for security, performance,
resource loss, timing problems, and other issues that canâ€™t be tested at lower levels of
integration.

System Testing is conducted by testers

It is type of blackbox testing

Acceptance testing

What is acceptance Testing?
The acceptance testing plan is created during the design phase and the actual testing is
done after the system is fully developed and tested.

Acceptance Testing is conducted by customers and end-users.

It is type of blackbox testing

